# AI Help Role Terminology Firewall

AI Help Assistant must never mix Agency, Client, and Model terminology.

## Canonical Role Labels

- Agency sessions: "You are using IndexCasting as an Agency."
- Client sessions: "You are using IndexCasting as a Client."
- Model sessions: only basic model account/profile/application/calendar guidance.

## Agency-Only Navigation

For Agency answers, only use visible Agency workspace labels:
`Dashboard`, `My Models`, `Clients`, `Messages`, `Calendar`, `Recruiting`, `Team`, `Links`, `Billing`, `Settings`.

Agency option/casting creation is always:
- `Calendar` -> `ADD OPTION` for options.
- `Calendar` -> `ADD CASTING` for castings.

Never tell an Agency user to create options/castings from `Roster`, `Discover`, `My Projects`, `Request option`, or `Request casting`.

## Client-Only Navigation

For Client answers, only use visible Client workspace labels:
`Dashboard`, `Discover`, `My Projects`, `Messages`, `Calendar`, `Agencies`, `Team`, `Billing`, `Profile`.

Client option/casting flow is request-based:
- `Discover` or `My Projects` -> `Request option`.
- `Discover` or `My Projects` -> `Request casting`.

Never tell a Client user to use `My Models`, `Clients`, `Recruiting`, `Links`, `ADD OPTION`, or `ADD CASTING`.

## Required Checks

- Any change to AI help copy/system prompts must include tests that prove Agency knowledge excludes Client-only terms and Client knowledge excludes Agency-only terms.
- Phase 2 live data is allowlist-only. Currently live intents are `calendar_summary`, `calendar_item_details`, Agency-only `model_visible_profile_facts`, and Agency-only `model_calendar_availability_check` (visible calendar conflicts only; not a final availability guarantee).
- **`phase2.ts` multilingual routing tokens:** Minimal deterministic patterns may map mixed German/English *phrasing* to the **existing** live intents above (same allowed RPC/facts contracts). Must **not** add new intents, broaden facts, bypass role gates, add billing/invoice/live payment access, or change the requirement that **all user-visible assistant prose stays English** (product rule: `.cursorrules` §4b).
- All other live-data intents remain forbidden, including messages, **billing/unified invoices/payments/subscriptions/offers**, team/invites, admin/security, database/RLS/schema questions, writes, hidden/private model data, emails, phone numbers, sync IDs, internal IDs, raw storage paths, file URLs, and private media.
- No `service_role`, no free SQL, no LLM-controlled tools, and no LLM-controlled table/RPC access. The Edge Function may call only narrow server-owned data sources and must send the LLM only minimized facts objects.
- `model_visible_profile_facts` is Agency-only and may expose only visible Agency UI facts: display name, visible city/country, height, chest, waist, hips, shoes, hair, eyes, categories, and `account_linked` as product wording.
- `model_visible_profile_facts` matching must scope to the verified Agency workspace first, then match visible model display names with case-/accent-tolerant exact, prefix, and partial matching. Ambiguous matches may show safe display names only.
- Model matching may use token/prefix/trigram-style fuzzy ranking only after the verified Agency-visible model set is scoped. Never fuzzy-match across all models or return hidden/cross-org candidates.
- `calendar_summary` and `calendar_item_details` must stay bounded by date/range, result limits, role/org context, and product labels only. Details may expose only visible date, start/end time, kind, title, model name, counterparty name, visible note/description, and safe product status label.
- AI assistant follow-up context must be short-lived, frontend-session-only, and minimized. It may contain one safe `last_calendar_item`, one safe `last_model_name`, single-resolution source markers, optional `pending_calendar_kind_prompt` after an ambiguous calendar follow-up (enables single-word job/casting/option/booking replies), `last_intent`, and non-sensitive created/expires timestamps, but never secrets, org identifiers, internal IDs, emails, phone numbers, raw SQL/RPC/table/RLS details, messages, file URLs, prices, billing, team/admin data, hidden notes, or write payloads. Context may be updated only for exactly one resolved visible calendar item or exactly one resolved visible model; stale, ambiguous, missing-source, or unrelated-query contexts must be cleared and force clarification.
- Persistent AI assistant rate limits are mandatory for every intent, including `help_static`, live intents, and forbidden/blocked attempts. Limits are server-side only, per-user and per-organization, and may use org-specific DB config resolved from authenticated org membership. Never trust client-provided counters, org IDs, query params, prompts, or frontend environment values for limits.
- The assistant must fail closed if the persistent limiter check fails. Do not call Mistral or live-data RPCs when the limiter is unavailable or has blocked the request.
- Usage logging may store only minimized metadata (user/org, role, intent, result, char counts, provider/model label, duration, sanitized error category). Never log or persist full prompts, full assistant answers, model names from prompts, calendar details, notes, messages, emails, phone numbers, secrets, access tokens, SQL, RPC/table/RLS details, file URLs, or returned internal IDs.
- Pricing, negotiation, `waiting_for`, `model_approval`, raw messages, billing, team/invite, admin/security, GDPR export/delete, service_role/free SQL, and write actions remain forbidden.
- New AI assistant SQL migrations must be narrow, org-scoped, grant only intended roles, revoke anon/PUBLIC, and be deployed without destructive migration repair. No new live-data intent may ship without persistent rate-limit coverage.
